<font color="#FF0000">GRID CO-ORDINATES</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jul 29 12:25:13 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I was created in God's image at Fort Sam Houston, Texas while the Creator was there on vacation from Heaven.  Since he couldn't make up his mind on a PCS (permanent change of station) for me I was assigned to live on the Red River which separates Oklahoma from Texas.  Actually, God created Texas so webfooted beach dwellers and hillbillies would have some place to go on R&amp;R.  <br>
When I was promoted from infant stud to young adult stud, I was assigned to B Dtry, 14th Arty, 2d AD.  I proposed a shoulder mounted, belt fed 155, and the old man got pissed.<br>
I became a medic.  I soon realized that they carry more stuff on their back and discovered what a bunch of sissies infantrymen really are, always complaining about sore feet and &quot;it hurts when I pee.&quot;  Wankan Tankan realizing that I had risen above the ranks of enlisted swine, decided to give me wings.  He made me a Warrant Officer and thereby authorized everyone to called me Chief without the attendant racial slur.  It backfired.  Legions of cannon fodder began calling me &quot;Chief, Chief.&quot;  After God had amused himself sufficiently, he elevated me to his own status and made me a Captain.<br>
After the war he sent me to Alaska as a bush pilot.  I became too inquisitive about why he had created Alaska more beautiful and much larger than Texas and he perceived me as being retarded.  Therefore, along with a couple hundred other severly impaired and retarded Texans, I was transplanted to Oklahoma.  God effectively doubled the I.Q. of both states.  Here, no one calls me Chief... if they do... everyone answers.  Actually, it is very confusing.<br><br>
They do make some good whiskey in Tennesse.  We use it to kill ants, tan hides and remove rust from our pickup trucks.<br>
Tennesse whiskey is okay if you go there, but don't drink the water.<br><br>
A Texan's greatest pleasure is to see an Okie headed North across the Red River with a U-Haul trailer.<br>
We view Yankees like hemorroids,  ...if they come down and go back up, it's okay.  If they come down and stay... then they are a real pain in the ass.<br>
Me... I believe in &quot;Maka Kin Le Mitawaca!&quot;  I own the earth.<br>
Thanks to all of you for protecting a piece of it for me and my kids, grandkids and numerous ex-wives.<br><br>
Mustang Two Four
